# Project Folder Structure

Follow the feature-sliced architecture. Never dump files in root-level catch-all folders.

## Client (`collab-canvas/client/src/`)

```
app/                        ← app shell, providers, router
  providers/AuthProvider.tsx
  router/index.tsx

components/                 ← UI components, grouped by domain
  shared/                   ← cross-cutting reusable UI (Button, Modal, Toast)
  canvas/                   ← canvas viewport, shape renderers, overlays
  toolbar/                  ← tool selection bar
  properties/               ← property editing panel
  presence/                 ← remote cursor rendering
  locking/                  ← lock indicator overlays
  auth/                     ← login/signup forms

features/                   ← state + logic, grouped by domain
  canvas/                   ← canvas store, data hooks
  elements/                 ← element store, mutations, realtime handlers
  auth/                     ← auth store
  presence/                 ← presence store
  locking/                  ← lock store, lock manager hook, lock handlers
  history/                  ← undo/redo store and hooks

hooks/                      ← shared hooks not tied to one feature
services/                   ← external communication
  api/                      ← REST API client + per-resource modules
  websocket/                ← WebSocket connection manager

pages/                      ← route-level page components (thin wrappers)
types/                      ← shared TypeScript interfaces and types
utils/                      ← pure helper functions (geometry, formatting)
```

## Placement Rules

- **New feature?** → create a folder under `features/` with its store, hooks, and handlers
- **New UI component?** → place under `components/<domain>/`; if used across 3+ domains, move to `components/shared/`
- **New API call?** → add to the relevant module in `services/api/` (e.g., `canvasApi.ts`), never inline `fetch()` in components
- **New type/interface?** → add to `types/` if shared across features; keep feature-local types in the feature folder
- **New page/route?** → add to `pages/`, keep it thin — delegate to components and hooks

## Server (`collab-canvas/server/app/`)

```
api/routes/                 ← FastAPI route handlers (thin — delegate to services)
core/                       ← config, security, shared middleware
db/                         ← session factory, base model
models/                     ← SQLAlchemy ORM models
schemas/                    ← Pydantic request/response schemas
services/                   ← business logic layer
websocket/                  ← WS connection manager, event router, auth
redis/                      ← Redis client helpers (presence, locks, pubsub)
tests/                      ← mirrors source structure (test_auth.py, etc.)
```

## Placement Rules

- **New endpoint?** → route in `api/routes/`, logic in `services/`, schema in `schemas/`
- **New DB table?** → model in `models/`, migration via Alembic
- **New Redis usage?** → helper in `redis/`, consumed by services
- **Never put business logic in route handlers** — routes parse input, call services, return responses
